PART: Budget Tracker
NAME: Budget Tracker
STATUS: draft

WHEN: Add Category
MARKER: add_category
INTENT: user adds a new budget category
TAGS: #form, #list, #user, #when
---
When the user taps the add category button, a form appears. The user fills in the category name and monthly limit. The new category is added to the list and its balance is set to zero.

WHEN: Update Category Balance
MARKER: update_category_balance
INTENT: user updates a category's balance
TAGS: #card, #form, #user, #when
---
When the user taps the edit icon on a category card, a form appears. The user can adjust the balance. The changes are saved and the category's balance is updated.

ASSERT: Category Limits
MARKER: category_limits
INTENT: ensure categories do not exceed their monthly limits
TAGS: #assert
---
A category's balance cannot exceed its monthly limit. If a category's balance reaches its limit, no further expenses can be added to that category until the next month.

SURFACE: Category Card
MARKER: category_card
INTENT: labels and styles for category cards
TAGS: #card, #surface
---
The category card displays the category name, current balance, and monthly limit. The card background color changes to red if the balance exceeds the limit.